•CENTERING AN ELEMENT WITH CSS•
/*Note: If the element is not a flexible item, the flex property has no effect.*/

<div class="parent">
    <p class="child">
        Example Text
    </p>
</div>

.parent{
       display: flex;
       justify-content: center;
       align-items: center;
  }


•HOW TO MAKE ROUNDED CORNERS•
<style type="text/css">
.round1 {
   border:1px solid #c1c13a; 
   -moz-border-radius: 10px;
   -webkit-border-radius: 10px;
   border-radius: 10px; /* future proofing */
   -khtml-border-radius: 10px; /* for old Konqueror browsers */
}
.round2 {
   border:1px solid #c1c13a; 
   -moz-border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0;
   -webkit-border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0;
   border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0; /* future proofing */
   -khtml-border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0; /* for old Konqueror browsers */
}
</style>

•EXAMPLE OF A LINEAR GRADIENT BACKGROUND CODE•
body {
background: #f06;
background: linear-gradient(45deg, #f06, yellow);
min-height: 100%;
}


